    <text>
        <body>
            <div type="edition">
                <div type="textpart">
                    <ab><persName key="#Archpriests"><name ref="Leo">Leo</name>
                            <rs key="#Archpriests">archipresbitero</rs></persName>, filio
                            <persName>bone memorie <name ref="Adalmannus"
                            >Adalmanni</name></persName>, pro anima ordina e conferma <persName
                            key="#Priests"><name ref="Leo">Leo</name>
                            <rs key="#Priests">presbitero</rs></persName> dilecto nepote meo, filio
                            <persName>bone memorie <name>Ildiprandi</name></persName> germano meo,
                        idest in ecclesia mea illa cui vocabulum est beate <orgName
                            ref="#juridical_persons/304">Sancte Marie et beati Sancti Michaeli
                            arcangeli adque beati Sancti Petri principis apostolorum</orgName> in
                            <placeName ref="#places/499">loco qui dicitur Brancalo</placeName>, ubi
                        vocitatur <placeName ref="#places/759">Purgatile</placeName>, quas mihi
                        pertenere videtur de hereditatem et subccessionem parentorum meorum; ideo
                        suprascripta ecclesia Sancte Marie et Sancti Mihaeli Archangeli adque beati
                        Sancti Petri cum casis et rebus domnicatis adque casis et rebus massariciis
                        (…), cum fundametis et omnem edefi seo curtis, teris, ecc. (…) una cum
                        notitia iudicati sive moniminas vel qualibet scriptiones cartarum ex ipsa
                        eccl(esia) et casis et rebus pertinentes sunt (…). Obbligo: in ipsa
                        eccl(esia) Sancte Marie ecc. per te aut per tuam dispositionem officium Dei
                        et luminaria adque incensum seo missarum solemnia fieri (…) et pro me et pro
                        animabus parentorum meorum Domini misericordia exorare debeas. Diritto di
                        presbitero ordinare et confirmare nella chiesa e nei suoi beni (cui
                        spetteranno i medesimi diritti e oneri), ut ipsa Domini eccl(esia) semper de
                        pbe ordinata sint, ut de ordinationem in ordinationem semper ordinata
                        permaneant et consistant usque in sempiternum seculi, ut Dei laudibus melius
                        ad melius adcrescat. Pena in duplum. quia in tali ordinem hanc ordinatjonis
                        cartula <persName key="#Writer #Notary"><name ref="Teudemundus"
                                >Teudimundum</name></persName>
                        <rs key="#Notary">notarium</rs> scribere rogavi. Actum <placeName
                            ref="#places/4">Luca</placeName>. </ab>
                    <ab>Sottoscrivono come <rs key="#Witness">testimoni</rs>: <persName
                            key="#Witness #Scabini"><name ref="Teudebrandus"
                            >Teuprandu</name></persName>
                        <rs key="#Scabini">schabinus</rs>, <persName key="#Witness #Notary"><name
                                ref="Leo">Leo</name>
                            <rs key="#Notary">notarius</rs></persName>, <persName
                            key="#Witness #Notary"><name ref="Gausbertus">Cospertus</name>
                            <rs key="#Notary">notarius</rs></persName>, <persName key="#Witness"
                                ><name ref="Ermipertus">Ermiperto</name></persName>, <persName
                            key="#Witness"><name ref="Leo">Leo</name></persName>, <persName
                            key="#Witness"><name ref="Gausfredus">Cosfridi</name></persName>,
                            <persName key="#Witness"><name ref="Giselbertus"
                            >Ghisalperto</name></persName>, <persName key="#Witness"><name
                                ref="Andreas">Andrea</name></persName>.</ab>
                </div>
            </div>
            <div type="bibliography" subtype="editions">
                <p>MDL, 5/2, n. 983, pp. 608; ChLA, 86, n. 26, pp. 92-95 </p>
            </div>
            <div type="bibliography" subtype="additional">
